Head of Music Curators [Full-Time]
Groover in a few lines
Groover is a web platform where artists submit their music to media, labels & music influencers for coverage and get guaranteed feedback.
Opportunity Review
We are looking for a Head of Music Curators to join our Business Team and work alongside with Dorian (co-founder of Groover). Your mission is to be sure all curators & music pros are well selected, activated, satisfied and retained on the groover.co platform. You we will also be in charge to grow the community of new music curators on Groover. Main goal: building an active of community of 5,000 curators and pros by December 2023 in North America, Europe and South America for all music genres
Mission
- Growth of our community of music curators and pros : keep on growing and building our community of curators in Europe, North and South America. In all music genres => Target to increase the community to 5K active curators (by Dec 2023) and 12K (by Dec 2025) - Managing and ensuring the satisfaction of our community of curators : simplify the onboarding and the activity of our curators, build events and process to help curators to become more and more active => Answer rate within the week of 90% for our community of active curators, NPS > 50, global enthusiasm for curators - Building and managing the network of local ambassadors in all the countries in which Groover is present : US, Canada, Italy, UK, Brazil and more. Ambassadors are in charge of sourcing and onboarding new curators locally. => Target to have a network of 1 active ambassador operating in each key city for Groover - Building the best community of curators to help artists: curators are the natural and organic leverage for artist satisfaction and growth => Target to keep our 25% acceptance rate
Who we are looking for
- You have a bilingual level in English. Ideally, you already worked out from France and you can work in a multi-cultural environment easily - You already gathered, structured and managed a community of thousands of active people in a previous experience by implementing process and events - You are organized and efficient - You have already managed or led a team - You have great relationship skills and a good natural communication - You're passionate about building a community, building a group around values and helping them makes you happy. - (Nice to have) You have a great understanding of the music industry, its people and dynamics
